<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-13T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1881: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-13T16:00:00-04:00">June 13,
                                    1942—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>154. Department’s 138, May 22 [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>]. War Department
                            prefers not to undertake organization of mission to Iran at this time.
                            Reasons given are: 1. Difficulty of releasing experienced officers for
                            such duty; 2. Primary responsibility of British for Middle Eastern
                            operations; 3. War Department doubts that foreign mission could have
                            much effect in correction abuses in Iranian Army.</p>
                        <p>However, it is understood General Greely will be instructed to make a
                            report upon all phases of situation, and if he recommends assignment of
                            additional officers further consideration will be given the
                            proposal.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>